7
00:00:54,929 --> 00:00:57,849
It's tree sap water from a painted maple.
My wife brought it.

8
00:00:57,932 --> 00:01:01,478
You moved here with your wife
while she's pregnant.

9
00:01:01,561 --> 00:01:03,897
So that must have been tough.
Especially during her first trimester.

10
00:01:05,065 --> 00:01:06,066
Thank you.

11
00:01:06,149 --> 00:01:10,695
The chief has been telling me
to make sure you're settling in well.

12
00:01:10,779 --> 00:01:13,656
Hey, do you have connections
with the CIA or something?

13
00:01:15,241 --> 00:01:17,410
Hey, I'm just joking.

14
00:01:17,494 --> 00:01:19,412
Here. Gosh. This is heavy.

15
00:01:19,496 --> 00:01:21,414
It's heavy. Oh boy.

16
00:01:34,552 --> 00:01:35,595
You're home.

17
00:01:36,513 --> 00:01:38,890
-What are you doing in the dark?
-Hi.

18
00:01:39,557 --> 00:01:41,935
What's the matter? Did something happen?

19
00:01:43,102 --> 00:01:46,314
-By the way, the captain…
-Honey. Could you sit down for a minute?

20
00:01:54,405 --> 00:01:55,490
What's going on?

21
00:01:57,826 --> 00:02:00,495
Someone came to visit us.

22
00:02:00,578 --> 00:02:03,414
Who? We just moved here.

23
00:02:03,998 --> 00:02:04,874
He's someone

24
00:02:05,875 --> 00:02:07,877
I knew from the One Family Welfare Center.

25
00:02:07,961 --> 00:02:10,088
I was close to him and his sister.

26
00:02:10,755 --> 00:02:12,298
He came over.

27
00:02:12,382 --> 00:02:13,925
Oh, really?

28
00:02:14,801 --> 00:02:17,554
You probably haven't seen him
in years, then.

29
00:02:17,637 --> 00:02:20,098
-Right.
-So why did he come by?

30
00:02:24,269 --> 00:02:26,521
He said he always wondered
how I was doing.

31
00:02:26,604 --> 00:02:28,857
And he knew that I've been living in Seoul

32
00:02:28,940 --> 00:02:30,900
after getting married. Also, he knows that

33
00:02:32,235 --> 00:02:34,028
I had just moved back here.

34
00:02:36,781 --> 00:02:38,116
He then said…

35
00:02:41,411 --> 00:02:42,620
he knew

36
00:02:44,205 --> 00:02:45,373
how much

37
00:02:46,916 --> 00:02:48,585
I despised

38
00:02:50,628 --> 00:02:52,213
my dad.

39
00:02:53,756 --> 00:02:56,718
He knew what my dad had done
at the welfare center

40
00:02:56,801 --> 00:02:59,345
and how I was trying to get as far away

41
00:03:01,848 --> 00:03:03,182
as I could from my dad.

42
00:03:08,146 --> 00:03:09,230
Really?

43
00:03:12,358 --> 00:03:14,152
I don't know what to say.

44
00:03:16,321 --> 00:03:18,448
Why is he bringing that up now?

45
00:03:20,074 --> 00:03:21,075
No.

46
00:03:21,743 --> 00:03:23,119
He mentioned it before.

47
00:03:24,621 --> 00:03:26,080
So you know, Honey.

48
00:03:28,583 --> 00:03:30,460
Can I ask you something?

49
00:03:31,377 --> 00:03:32,545
Promise me

50
00:03:34,714 --> 00:03:36,466
that you'll tell me the truth.

51
00:03:39,552 --> 00:03:40,678
I will.

52
00:03:41,638 --> 00:03:42,805
What's the question?

53
00:03:45,850 --> 00:03:47,810
You really don't remember anything…

54
00:03:51,022 --> 00:03:53,274
after the car accident, right?

55
00:03:53,358 --> 00:03:54,442
What?

56
00:03:55,652 --> 00:03:57,070
What kind of question is that?

57
00:03:57,153 --> 00:04:00,698
You said you can't remember at all
what you did in Seoul.

58
00:04:04,994 --> 00:04:06,704
Can I trust you when you say that?

59
00:04:21,636 --> 00:04:23,054
So her death

60
00:04:25,098 --> 00:04:26,557
wasn't in vain.

61
00:04:29,102 --> 00:04:31,396
She had a baby before she died.

62
00:04:33,356 --> 00:04:34,524
To start

63
00:04:35,566 --> 00:04:36,818
a new life with me

64
00:04:37,777 --> 00:04:39,404
and to usher in a new beginning.

65
00:04:42,865 --> 00:04:43,992
Understand?

66
00:04:44,993 --> 00:04:46,619
It wasn't you.

67
00:04:48,413 --> 00:04:50,206
I was the one she loved in the end.

68
