Everybody knows about
the rampant abuse that went on

121
00:14:05,386 --> 00:14:06,637
at the One Family Welfare Center.

122
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:09,098
That's a gross misrepresentation.

123
00:14:09,765 --> 00:14:11,684
For political reasons,

124
00:14:11,767 --> 00:14:14,728
a lot of the facts about
the welfare center were misconstrued.

125
00:14:15,479 --> 00:14:17,314
So how were we able to leave the center?

126
00:14:17,898 --> 00:14:19,149
That bastard and me.

127
00:14:20,234 --> 00:14:22,736
Kids weren't allowed to leave
that facility even if they wanted to.

128
00:14:23,863 --> 00:14:27,658
There was a nice married couple
who worked in the cafeteria

129
00:14:28,450 --> 00:14:30,578
at the welfare center.

130
00:14:30,661 --> 00:14:33,831
Unfortunately, they weren't
able to have kids.

131
00:14:33,914 --> 00:14:37,835
They were very fond of you,
Ms. Jo Jung-hyun.

132
00:14:38,752 --> 00:14:42,172
So they said they wanted to adopt you.

133
00:14:42,256 --> 00:14:45,259
That's Ms. Jung Kyung-sook
and her husband.

134
00:14:47,303 --> 00:14:48,679
Thanks to the welfare center,

135
00:14:49,346 --> 00:14:51,932
you were able to meet them,

136
00:14:52,016 --> 00:14:55,561
and have a family of your own.

137
00:14:55,644 --> 00:14:56,937
Not that story.

138
00:14:58,939 --> 00:15:01,775
I'm asking you about the real reason

139
00:15:01,859 --> 00:15:04,111
we were able to escape from the facility.

140
00:15:21,170 --> 00:15:24,089
Oh gosh. This is so sudden.

141
00:15:24,840 --> 00:15:27,468
How did this conversation
take a sudden turn?

142
00:15:28,427 --> 00:15:30,554
I'm the one who invited you here.

143
00:15:31,180 --> 00:15:33,724
How come you're asking
more questions than me, Ms. Jo?

144
00:15:33,807 --> 00:15:34,850
That's odd.

145
00:15:36,018 --> 00:15:37,561
That's not right.

146
00:15:38,270 --> 00:15:39,730
It's completely unfair.

147
00:15:40,856 --> 00:15:44,318
Let's stop wasting time
since we're both busy people.

148
00:15:44,818 --> 00:15:47,738
I'll get straight to the point.
I have a straightforward demand.

149
00:15:48,238 --> 00:15:50,866
Ms. Jo, stop snooping around.

150
00:15:52,201 --> 00:15:55,663
You're tracing past events
after discovering the 1987 magazine issue.

151
00:15:55,746 --> 00:15:57,289
I want you to stop that.

152
00:15:57,998 --> 00:16:00,960
Until I find Jae-young, I won't stop.

153
00:16:01,043 --> 00:16:02,002
You won't?

154
00:16:05,631 --> 00:16:08,759
I knew you would say no.

155
00:16:10,678 --> 00:16:13,263
Speaking of which…

156
00:16:14,306 --> 00:16:16,058
How about this?

157
00:16:16,141 --> 00:16:19,436
I'm willing to
help you find your niece, Ms. Jo.

158
00:16:24,149 --> 00:16:25,567
What are you talking about?

159
00:16:26,944 --> 00:16:27,945
You're…

160
00:16:29,071 --> 00:16:30,531
part of the cult too.

161
00:16:33,826 --> 00:16:35,160
Oh my gosh.

162
00:16:35,828 --> 00:16:38,497
Life isn't so simple, is it?

163
00:16:38,580 --> 00:16:42,209
That's why you're here talking to me.

164
00:16:42,292 --> 00:16:44,503
I'm talking about opening
new opportunities for both of us.

165
00:16:47,131 --> 00:16:48,757
What's going on?

166
00:16:48,841 --> 00:16:51,051
Old lady. Come here.

167
00:16:53,178 --> 00:16:54,430
What happened?

168
00:16:55,889 --> 00:16:57,099
Who are you?

169
00:16:58,017 --> 00:16:59,560
Which department are you from?

170
00:16:59,643 --> 00:17:00,561
Well…

171
00:17:02,146 --> 00:17:03,772
Hello Detective Choi.

172
00:17:05,065 --> 00:17:07,860
The MIU said they were on their way.
You got here fast.

173
00:17:07,943 --> 00:17:09,737
I was in the area,
so I came straight here.

174
00:17:09,820 --> 00:17:11,947
-Can I go in?
-Sure. Go ahead.

175
00:17:12,031 --> 00:17:14,158
-This way.
-How could this happen?

176
00:17:24,418 --> 00:17:27,880
-Did a team sweep the place already?
-No, we're the first to come.

177
00:17:28,589 --> 00:17:30,174
The crime scene is untouched.

178
00:18:09,088 --> 00:18:11,924
Oh my goodness. How terrible.

179
00:18:14,384 --> 00:18:16,428
Oh my goodness.

180
00:18:21,517 --> 00:18:24,645
FORENSIC INVESTIGATION

181
00:18:33,070 --> 00:18:35,489
All hell will break loose soon.

182
00:18:36,782 --> 00:18:39,451
These cult members are lunatics.

183
00:18:40,119 --> 00:18:42,579
They're going to commit extreme acts.

184
00:18:42,663 --> 00:18:43,997
What kind of acts?

185
00:18:45,124 --> 00:18:47,793
You understand that
I can't tell you the specifics, right?

186
00:18:49,169 --> 00:18:51,547
But I can tell you this.

187
00:18:52,881 --> 00:18:54,133
The end of the future.

188
00:18:55,300 --> 00:18:56,635
That day is coming.

189
00:18:57,886 --> 00:19:00,472
They'll commit another attack
like the one in 1987.

190
00:19:01,682 --> 00:19:03,350
Only those who are purified

191
00:19:03,976 --> 00:19:05,644
can see that day together.

192
00:19:10,190 --> 00:19:13,402
It's completely crazy.

193
00:19:14,695 --> 00:19:16,864
I can't give you the details about it.

194
00:19:17,531 --> 00:19:20,826
But it's a total waste of time
and energy. Worthless.

195
00:19:22,828 --> 00:19:24,371
So what are you trying to tell me?

196
00:19:27,332 --> 00:19:29,668
So… You need to…

197
00:19:31,253 --> 00:19:34,840
keep your distance
from them and just observe.

198
00:19:44,683 --> 00:19:49,104
I'm upset over the senseless things
they're doing.

199
00:19:50,105 --> 00:19:52,649
I'm sure he would not approve of

200
