what is going on right now in the cult.

201
00:19:58,530 --> 00:19:59,740
So…

202
00:20:00,908 --> 00:20:03,535
I'm planning to flip the script.

203
00:20:04,828 --> 00:20:08,332
And I need your help to do that, Ms. Jo.

204
00:20:09,416 --> 00:20:11,668
I'll keep my promise.

205
00:20:11,752 --> 00:20:14,046
If you agree to cooperate with me,

206
00:20:14,713 --> 00:20:17,883
I'll make sure that
Jae-young is returned to her home.

207
00:20:18,467 --> 00:20:19,885
Do you understand?

208
00:20:22,971 --> 00:20:24,264
How can I trust you?

209
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:36,610
What is

210
00:20:37,861 --> 00:20:40,864
most important to you right now,
Ms. Jo? Think about that.

211
00:20:42,366 --> 00:20:43,617
Besides that,

212
00:20:44,534 --> 00:20:46,870
nothing else matters to you, right?

213
00:20:49,539 --> 00:20:50,958
Sail that doesn't bend…

214
00:20:52,876 --> 00:20:55,087
break in the storm, you know.

215
00:21:04,096 --> 00:21:06,014
I'm not here to talk about anything else.

216
00:21:06,098 --> 00:21:09,309
You need to know what really happened to
to Associate Professor Kim, don't you?

217
00:21:09,393 --> 00:21:11,561
Please leave.
I don't want to hear it right now.

218
00:21:12,479 --> 00:21:14,022
Professor!

219
00:21:14,106 --> 00:21:15,899
Why are you suddenly being like this?

220
00:21:15,983 --> 00:21:17,776
Do you really have to ask?

221
00:21:17,859 --> 00:21:20,153
I read the article about you
in the morning paper.

222
00:21:20,237 --> 00:21:23,782
How can I continue working with
someone like you?

223
00:21:23,865 --> 00:21:27,369
I'll send the interview files
separately to the precinct.

224
00:21:27,452 --> 00:21:28,787
So please leave.

225
00:21:51,310 --> 00:21:53,937
Why is that car honking?
It's hurting my ears.

226
00:21:54,021 --> 00:21:56,148
I'm getting a massive headache.

227
00:21:56,648 --> 00:21:58,859
And why is General Affairs telling me
to get rid of it?

228
00:22:00,068 --> 00:22:02,279
They don't even know what it is.

229
00:22:23,800 --> 00:22:25,510
Yes? This is Koo Byung-min.

230
00:22:25,594 --> 00:22:27,929
Oh, Dr. Ahn. You're here?

231
00:22:28,013 --> 00:22:31,224
I'll meet you at the parking lot
right away.

232
00:22:45,781 --> 00:22:47,741
-Yes!
-Why didn't you go easy on me?

233
00:22:47,824 --> 00:22:49,451
You lost so no complaining.

234
00:22:50,160 --> 00:22:51,161
Next.

235
00:22:52,162 --> 00:22:54,456
Oh, it's your first day, isn't it?

236
00:22:55,248 --> 00:22:57,459
I like your spirit. Get ready.

237
00:23:01,296 --> 00:23:03,048
Oh, hi. Just a minute.

238
00:23:08,845 --> 00:23:10,222
You're so mean.

239
00:23:10,305 --> 00:23:11,807
Tough luck. You lost.

240
00:23:11,890 --> 00:23:14,142
You're all doing poorly.

241
